    • Method Detail

      • run

        void run(boolean codeIsCorrect,
         APlayer player,
         String realCode,
         String typedCode)
        Performs operations based on a digicode operation result.
        Parameters:
        codeIsCorrect - 'true' if the code given by the player matches, 'false' otherwise.
        player - The player who completed the operation.
        realCode - The code requested to be typed by the player.
        typedCode - The code the player has entered.

      • failed

        default void failed(APlayer player,
                    String realCode,
                    String currentCode)
        Called when a given player exits the view without completing the code.
        Parameters:
        player - The player who cancelled the operation.
        realCode - The correct code.
        currentCode - The code the has typed right before canceling.

      • update

        default void update(APlayer player,
                    String realCode,
                    String currentCode)
        Called each times a given players enters or remove a digit in it's current view.
        Parameters:
        player - The player in operation.
        realCode - The code requested to be typed by the player.
        currentCode - The actual code the player has given.
